The Yoruba Youth Socio-cultural Association (YYSA) Worldwide has described the step taken in the South East by the northern leaders, Livestock and Perishable Goods Market Traders and Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association to ban herders who do not have families in the region from grazing as commendable. The commendation was contained in a statement made available to The Guardian yesterday in Ibadan by its National President, Olalekan Hammed. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .